Scope of the Reference Implementation

This release includes:

financial transaction structures
debit/credit pairing models
structural resolution logic
demo applications (Python + HTML)
outputs and reference outputs
validation traces

ORL-Money defines a deterministic financial model where correctness emerges from structure:

resolve(structure) ->
    RESOLVED     if complete and consistent
    INCOMPLETE   if required parts are missing
    ABSTAIN      if structure is conflicting

What This Demonstrates

• financial correctness from fragmented inputs
• independence from transaction ordering
• independence from timestamps and synchronized clocks
• safe handling of incomplete financial data
• conflict containment without corruption
• deterministic convergence across independent nodes
• reproducible outcomes

Conformance

An implementation is considered compatible if it preserves:

structure-based correctness
independence from order as authority
independence from synchronized time
deterministic convergence
reproducibility under equivalent inputs
explicit INCOMPLETE and ABSTAIN handling

Conformance is judged by observable behavior, not internal implementation.

Relationship to Shunyaya Framework

ORL-Money is part of the broader Shunyaya Structural Universal Mathematics (SSUM) framework.

It builds on:

STOCRS → structure-first computation
SSUM-Time → time independence
ORL → structural ledger truth

