Closing Statement

ORL-Money explores a fundamental possibility:

Financial correctness can emerge from structure, not from time, order, or synchronization.

It is released openly to encourage:

independent validation
real-world testing
safe experimentation
broader adoption of structure-first systems

Money systems, traditionally governed by sequence and timing, may also be understood as processes of structural validation.

ORL-Money is offered as a reference model for that shift.
